**Strategic Ledger (Prioritized Improvements)**

[P1] Implement Constitutional Fidelity Routing to enforce Safety > 0.98 and Fidelity > 0.95 thresholds
[P2] Enhance Adaptive Sampling & Backoff with deterministic exponential backoff execution
[P3] Refactor Dependency Injection Containerization using Service Locator or DI container
[P4] Introduce Immutable Telemetry using Maximum Trace Visibility
[P5] Upgrade Repository Pattern with enhanced data persistence for role-bound Read/Write streams

**DNA Signature Update (New Properties & Methods)**

To ensure a seamless evolution, introduce the following new properties and methods:

1.  **Fidelity Evaluation:** Implement the `calculateFidelity()` method to assess the evaluation of cognitive actions.
      private calculateFidelity(cognitiveAction: CognitiveAction): number {
    // Implement business logic for fidelity calculation
    return cognitiveAction.fidelity;
  }

2.  **Adaptive Sampling:** Update the `cancelTokens()` method to incorporate deterministic exponential backoff execution.
      private cancelTokens(token: DisposableToken | null, delay: number): Promise<void> {
    if (token instanceof DisposableToken) {
      return this.cancelTokens(token, delay * Math.pow(2, attempt)).then(() => {
        if (token.disposed) {
          this._resourcesToRemove?.push(token);
        }
      });
    } else if (token.cancel) {
      return this.cancelTokens(token, delay * Math.pow(2, attempt)).then();
    } else {
      return Promise.resolve();
    }
  }

3.  **Dependency Injection Containerization:** Refactor the `DisposableToken` constructor to utilize a service locator or DI container.
      constructor(protected readonly container: ServiceLocator, linkedToken?: DisposableToken) {
    this._linkedToken = linkedToken;
  }

4.  **Immutable Telemetry:** Introduce the `recordMetric()` method to collect telemetry metadata natively.
      private recordMetric(event: Event): void {
    this.eventBus.emit('Trace', event);
  }

5.  **Repository Pattern:** Upgrade the `getRepository()` method to persist data with role-bound Read/Write streams.
      private getRepository(role: Role): any {
    // Implement business logic for data persistence
    return this.container.getRepository(role);
  }

**Strategic Reorganization (File Realignment)**

To maintain a cohesive architecture, reorganize the code as follows:

1.  Move `calculateFidelity()` and `recordMetric()` methods to a dedicated `Evaluator` class.
      class Evaluator {
    private readonly container: ServiceLocator;

    constructor(container: ServiceLocator) {
      this.container = container;
    }

    calculateFidelity(cognitiveAction: CognitiveAction): number {
      // Implement business logic for fidelity calculation
      return cognitiveAction.fidelity;
    }

    recordMetric(event: Event): void {
      this.container.eventBus.emit('Trace', event);
    }
  }

2.  Update `DisposableTokenFactory` to utilize the `Evaluator` class for fidelity evaluation and telemetry recording.
      class DisposableTokenFactory {
    private readonly container: ServiceLocator;

    constructor(container: ServiceLocator) {
      this.container = container;
    }

    createDefaultDisposableToken(eventBus: EventBus, linkedToken?: DisposableToken): DisposableToken {
      return new DisposableToken(eventBus, linkedToken, this.container.getEvaluator());
    }
  }

**Evolved Code (Refactored Structure & Methods)**

Apply the strategic improvements and reorganization:

// DisposableToken class
class DisposableToken {
  // ... existing methods ...

  dispose(): void {
    this.recordMetric(DisposableToken.DISCARD_TOKEN_EVENT);
    this._resourcesToRemove?.forEach(resource => {
      this.eventBus.removeListener(DisposableToken.DISCARD_TOKEN_EVENT, resource.dispose);
    });
    this._disposed = true;
  }

  private recordMetric(event: Event): void {
    this.eventBus.emit('Trace', event);
  }
}

// Evaluator class
class Evaluator {
  private readonly container: ServiceLocator;

  constructor(container: ServiceLocator) {
    this.container = container;
  }

  calculateFidelity(cognitiveAction: CognitiveAction): number {
    // Implement business logic for fidelity calculation
    return cognitiveAction.fidelity;
  }

  recordMetric(event: Event): void {
    this.container.eventBus.emit('Trace', event);
  }
}

// DisposableTokenFactory class
class DisposableTokenFactory {
  private readonly container: ServiceLocator;

  constructor(container: ServiceLocator) {
    this.container = container;
  }

  createDefaultDisposableToken(eventBus: EventBus, linkedToken?: DisposableToken): DisposableToken {
    return new DisposableToken(eventBus, linkedToken, this.container.getEvaluator());
  }

  getOrCreate(id: string): DisposableToken | null {
    const token = this.container.getRepository('linkedTokens').get(id);
    if (token) return token;
    return this.createDefaultDisposableToken(this.container.eventBus, null);
  }
}

